2026-04-21 01:30:59 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Input Cable (+) 6', 'Control Module 6'] hypothesis_explanation='The positive conductor of Control Input Cable (+) 6 has its ‘n’ side floating and is not terminated on Control Switch 6, while the negative and both output conductors are connected through. This means the series 12V path is interrupted at Control Module 6: upstream modules and their LEDs may still receive power, but no current can pass through the open 12V line at module 6 to energize downstream modules or the load. Consequently, the lamp and downstream indicators cannot turn on even with all switches ON. Repairing/terminating the floating 12V input conductor of Control Module 6 to the switch (or replacing this cable/module assembly if faulty) should restore continuity of the 12V rail and allow the lamp to operate correctly.'
